    <h2 class="section-heading">Our BDRs</h2>
    <p class="section-byline">Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet consectetur adipisicing elit</p>
    <div class="section-content flex-column">
      <p>
        First and foremost, they are immutable. Once a BDR is written, it cannot be modified or removed.
        To alter or "undo" a BDR, nilenso must create another new, immutable BDR. Second, they are
        historical. Because BDRs cannot be modified, they do not represent a policy and they are not a
        living document. They may of course point to a policy or living document which represents the
        most current version of the decision.
      </p>
      <p>
        BDRs are used to identify decision points for high-level strategy, policy, and company
        principles. They should not be used to describe or document specific actions the company or its
        employees take.
      </p>
